item.title: Decompiler?
item.dc:creator: @unlimitedorb unlimitedorb
item.description:
@unlimitedorb wrote:

[quote=“nueb35, post:16, topic:260345”][quote author=Fat Cookies link=topic=343733.msg2656984#msg2656984 date=1233941587]

The only other decompiler is JODE, which you can get for free here:
http://jode.sourceforge.net/

I was just wondering why he used a complier which you have to pay for? I remember using DJ Complier becuase I thought it would be better than JAD but then i realised it was just JAD with a GUI.

[/quote]

ill assume you mean decompiler, also best decompiler ive used would be Cavaj try that one (also when i say best decompiler i mean only decompiler)[/quote]

Decompilers and Compilers are basically the same concept i.e., translating a source language into a target language. In fact, if a person wants to learn how to design a decompiler their best bet is picking up a book on Compiling (seven months ago I decided to delve into this topic, and that’s what I’m still doing.) The only material I’ve found specifically on the topic of “decompiling” is contrived with toy examples. Admittedly, it took me a while to wrap my head around the fact that they are virtually the same topic so I was lost for quite a while. Hopefully, nobody here would make the same mistake
